Package ohos.event.notification

Class ReminderRequestAlarm

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.event.notification.ReminderRequest
      • ohos.event.notification.ReminderRequestAlarm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<ReminderRequest>, Sequenceable

    public class ReminderRequestAlarm
extends ReminderRequest
    A ReminderRequest child class used for creating reminders for alarm clocks.

    You can use this class to publish alarm reminders at a specified time (accurate to minute) on a particular day or on particular days every week.

    Since:
    6

    • Constructor Detail

      • ReminderRequestAlarm

        public ReminderRequestAlarm​(int hour,
                            int minute,
                            int[] daysOfWeek)
        A constructor used to create a ReminderRequestAlarm instance. The alarm reminder will be triggered at a specified time.

        Ensure that the input parameters meet the following requirements. Otherwise, the application may crash due to an illegal parameter exception.

        • The value of hour must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 23.
        • The value of minute must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to 59.
        • The length of the daysOfWeek array cannot be greater than 7.
        Parameters:
        hour - Indicates the hour for this alarm reminder. The value ranges from 0 to 23.
        minute - Indicates the minute for this alarm reminder. The value ranges from 0 to 59.
        daysOfWeek - Indicates the days in a week when this alarm reminder will be triggered. For example, the value {1, 3} indicates that the reminder will be triggered every Monday and Wednesday. By default, this reminder is not snoozed. You can call ReminderRequest.setTimeInterval(long) to set the snooze interval. If a snooze interval is set, this reminder will be snoozed for three times by default. You can call ReminderRequest.setSnoozeTimes(int) to change the snooze times.
        Since:
        6
